lead_paragraph: SOUTH BAY, Fla. — Out here in western Palm Beach County, Lake Okeechobee meets vestiges of theFlorida Everglades and, more significantly, a vast sugar growing area that encompasses hundreds of square miles. Over the years, the Everglades has shrunk into a corner of the state and the sugar region has grown, with detrimental effects on both water quality and the health of thehuge swamp.
headline_main: Trump Budget Plan Calls for $250M for Florida Everglades
headline_print_headline: Trump Budget Plan Calls for $250M for Florida Everglades

abstract: The president granted full pardons to seven people and commutations to four others on Tuesday. Here’s who they are.
snippet: The president granted full pardons to seven people and commutations to four others on Tuesday. Here’s who they are.
lead_paragraph: President Trump pardoned seven people on Tuesday, including the “junk bond king” Michael R. Milken and Bernard B. Kerik, a former New York City police commissioner. He also commuted the sentences of Rod R. Blagojevich, a former governor of Illinois, and three others.

abstract: In a party that’s shifted leftward on abortion rights, Democratic presidential hopefuls are offering different approaches to a central challenge: how to talk to voters without a clear home in the polarizing debate over the government’s role in the decision to end a pregnancy.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — In a party that’s shifted leftward on abortion rights, Democratic presidential hopefuls are offering different approaches to a central challenge: how to talk to voters without a clear home in the polarizing debate over the government’s role in the decision to end a pregnancy.

abstract: Rod Blagojevich returned home to Chicago early Wednesday, shaking hands and signing autographs after President Donald Trump cut short the 14-year prison sentence handed to the former Illinois governor for political corruption.
snippet: Rod Blagojevich returned home to Chicago early Wednesday, shaking hands and signing autographs after President Donald Trump cut short the 14-year prison sentence handed to the former Illinois governor for political corruption.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Rod Blagojevich returned home to Chicago early Wednesday, shaking hands and signing autographs after President Donald Trump cut short the 14-year prison sentence handed to the former Illinois governor for political corruption.
headline_main: Ex-Gov. Blagojevich Returns to Chicago, Maintains Innocence
headline_print_headline: Ex-Gov. Blagojevich Returns to Chicago, Maintains Innocence

abstract: Amazon is pointing the finger right at the president over the awarding of the JEDI military contract.

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday that he knew the identity of an anonymous Trump administration official who wrote an essay for the New York Times and later a book about efforts from within to thwart parts of the president's agenda to protect the country from his worst impulses.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday that he knew the identity of an anonymous Trump administration official who wrote an essay for the New York Times and later a book about efforts from within to thwart parts of the president's agenda to protect the country from his worst impulses.
headline_main: Trump Says He Knows Identity of Author Known as 'Anonymous'
headline_print_headline: Trump Says He Knows Identity of Author Known as 'Anonymous'
